Distribution.
Central Paratethys. A ubiquitous species in the Paratethys; the following list provides just some examples. Ottnangian (early Miocene): 
Switzerland
(
Rutsch 1929
); Badenian (middle Miocene): 
North Alpine Foreland Basin
: Platt (
Austria
) (
Sieber 1960
); 
Carpathian Foreland Basin
: Borač, Boskovice, Drnovice, Jaroměřice nad Rokytnou, Jerutek at Lysice, Lysice, Rudice (
Czech Republic
); Korytnica, Gliwice Stare, Małoszów, Józefów, Benc- zyn, Żegocina, Skoczów, Bogucice, Brzeźnica, Zgłobice, Gliwice (
Poland
) (
Quitzow 1922
; 
Bałuk 1975
); 

Vienna
Basin

